com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.interfaces

Interface TriPredicate<T,U,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - T the first type to test
    U - U the second type to test
    V - V the third type tot test
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface TriPredicate<T,U,V>
    This interface is created equally to the Predicate, but excepting 3 types as arguments

    Its primary use is to enable the ReceivePipelineCondition, which utilizes this predicate to evaluate whether or not an OnReceiveTriple should be executed or not.

    Since:
    1.0
    Version:
    1.0

      • and

        default TriPredicate<T,U,V> and(TriPredicate<? super T,? super U,? super V> other)
        Returns a composed triPredicate that represents a short-circuiting logical AND of this predicate and another. When evaluating the composed triPredicate, if this triPredicate is false, then the other triPredicate is not evaluated.

        Any exceptions thrown during evaluation of either triPredicate are relayed to the caller; if evaluation of this triPredicate throws an exception, the other triPredicate will not be evaluated.

        Parameters:
        other - a triPredicate that will be logically-ANDed with this predicate
        Returns:
        a composed triPredicate that represents the short-circuiting logical AND of this predicate and the other triPredicate
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null

      • negate

      • or

        default TriPredicate<T,U,V> or(TriPredicate<? super T,? super U,? super V> other)
        Returns a composed triPredicate that represents a short-circuiting logical OR of this triPredicate and another. When evaluating the composed triPredicate, if this predicate is true, then the other triPredicate is not evaluated.

        Any exceptions thrown during evaluation of either triPredicate are relayed to the caller; if evaluation of this triPredicate throws an exception, the other triPredicate will not be evaluated.

        Parameters:
        other - a triPredicate that will be logically-ORed with this triPredicate
        Returns:
        a composed triPredicate that represents the short-circuiting logical OR of this triPredicate and the other predicate
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null
